      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thinking about some of the code-gen implications here. Not a deal breaker, but do we have ideas to make this better in a future CL. Consider:\n\nvoid main() {\n  float4 arr[4];\n  ...\n  arr[1] +\u003d arr[2];\n}\n\nI think that\u0027s going to generate the address computation sequence 12 times (?). Having vectorized operations will help (only three address calculations). Just something to consider. (Ah, as I re-read the code, I realized that the passed-in location will have pre-computed the address up through the indexing, so it\u0027s just the offset portion that will be replicated). So this is less bad than I thought, and vectorized ops will essentially remove all the overhead.",
